==English==

===Etymology===
Before the days of instant pregnancy test, a woman's sample was injected into a rabbit - if the pregnancy hormone was present in the sample, the rabbit would die in short order.

===Phrase===
'''[[kill]] [[the]] [[rabbit]]'''
# {{dated}}, {{idiom}}: to get a positive test result from an old-fashioned pregnancy test.
#:''"What about her?"  "She '''killed the rabbit'''."''